# Design-anchor Self-Check (execute before each round of modifications ends)

0. **Directory**: Business pages and routes go in the **project's own** `src/` (or app directory). The component library and tokens live only inside `./.anchor/` (the hidden Design-anchor directory). Do not put business features inside `.anchor/`.
1. **Imports**: In business code, prefer `import { … } from "@design"` (alias configured per `ANCHOR_INTEGRATION.md`); otherwise import from `./.anchor/src/components/base/`. Do not hand-write native controls when a base component exists.
2. **Forbidden tags**: Check whether `<button>`, `<input>`, `<table>`, or any tag declared as `forbidden` in `*.spec.json` is used in business JSX; replace with the corresponding base component.
3. **Token-sensitive styling**: Avoid arbitrary-value Tailwind on prefixes `bg / text / border / ring / fill / stroke / from / to / via / shadow / p / m / gap / rounded`. Use semantic classes (`bg-primary`, `p-4`) or `var(--token)`. One-off layout (`w / h / top / left / grid-cols / aspect / z`) is fine with `[value]`.
4. **Image reference**: If the user provided a screenshot/mockup, you should have already chosen Path A (extract tokens) or Path B (follow existing tokens). Never silently invent hex values from the image. See `src/anchor/rules/AGENTS_IMAGE_REFERENCE.md`.
5. **Wrap-up**: If a Design-anchor Cursor Hook is configured, audit runs on save automatically. Otherwise proactively run `anchor audit` (or MCP `run_audit`) and fix issues based on the output.

If the user explicitly requests an exception or the spec does not yet cover the scenario, briefly explain the deviation in your reply and suggest updating `*.spec.json` and running `sync:anchor`.
